com.ckeiner.testbddy.core.bdd.scenario

Class ScenarioOutline<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ckeiner.testbddy.core.bdd.scenario.AbstractScenario

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the Testdata.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Statusable

    public class ScenarioOutline<T>
extends AbstractScenario
    Represents a Scenario Outline in the BDD Hierarchy.
    It is the same as a Scenario except that it has test data. This means, that the scenario gets executed once with each test data. To execute it, see the test() method.
    Author:
    ckeiner

    • Method Detail

      • test

        public void test()
        Executes the scenario outline.
        Exceptions and errors get caught and the scenario is executed with the rest of the test data. In the end, the exceptions and errors are re-thrown as ScenarioException and ScenarioError respectively.
        Should both, an exception and an error, occur, a ScenarioException is thrown.
        Specified by:
        test in class AbstractScenario
